  "prompt": "What are the all time best hollywood movies?",
  "response": "There are countless great Hollywood movies, and opinions on the \"best\" can vary widely depending on personal taste and criteria. However, some films are frequently cited by critics, filmmakers, and audiences as among the best due to their influence, craftsmanship, and enduring popularity. Here are some of the most acclaimed Hollywood movies of all time:\n\n1. **Citizen Kane (1941)** - Directed by Orson Welles\n2. **The Godfather (1972)** - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola\n3. **Casablanca (1942)** - Directed by Michael Curtiz\n4. **Gone with the Wind (1939)** - Directed by Victor Fleming\n5. **Lawrence of Arabia (1962)** - Directed by David Lean\n6. **Schindler's List (1993)** - Directed by Steven Spielberg\n7. **Psycho (1960)** - Directed by Alfred Hitchcock\n8. **12 Angry Men (1957)** - Directed by Sidney Lumet\n9. **The Shawshank Redemption (1994)** - Directed by Frank Darabont\n10. **Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope (1977)** - Directed by George Lucas\n11. **Pulp Fiction (1994)** - Directed by Quentin Tarantino\n12. **The Dark Knight (2008)** - Directed by Christopher Nolan\n13. **Forrest Gump (1994)** - Directed by Robert Zemeckis\n14. **One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest (1975)** - Directed by Milo\u0161 Forman\n15. **The Silence of the Lambs (1991)** - Directed by Jonathan Demme\n16. **The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King (2003)** - Directed by Peter Jackson\n17. **Vertigo (1958)** - Directed by Alfred Hitchcock\n18. **Goodfellas (1990)** - Directed by Martin Scorsese\n19. **Fight Club (1999)** - Directed by David Fincher\n20. **Inception (2010)** - Directed by Christopher Nolan\n\nThese films are celebrated for their storytelling, direction, performances, and overall impact on cinema. They have garnered critical acclaim, won numerous awards, and remain influential in the industry.",
